{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionClinical trials are essential for advancing medical knowledge and introducing new treatment paradigms.",
    "However, many eligible patients miss out on participating in these trials due to a lack of discussion with their treatment teams, a problem rooted in challenges, such as resource scarcity for patient screening [1,5].",
    "Screening is often manual and inefficient, consuming up to 45 minutes per patient and contributing to a 3-9 hour process for a single enrollment [12].",
    "Physicians, nurses, and research staff highlight time constraints and inadequate support as key obstacles [4,6].",
    "This situation contributes to low enrollment rates, leading to the premature closure of studies and limiting the scope of their findings [13]."
  ]
}